## Pattern Analysis Report: FlowGuard Modal & Axios Patterns

### 1. Create/Edit Modal Structure (Users.jsx)

**State Management:**
```javascript
const [modal, setModal] = useState({ isOpen: false, user: null, action: null });
```
- Simple object-based state with three properties: `isOpen` (boolean), `user` (data object), `action` (string - 'suspend' or 'delete')
- No separate form field state needed in this case (confirmation modals only)

**Modal Operations:**
- `openModal(user, action)` - opens with a specific user and action type
- `closeModal()` - closes and resets state to defaults
- `handleConfirmAction()` - async submit handler that validates and makes the API call

**Submit Handler Pattern:**
```javascript
const handleConfirmAction = async () => {
  const { id, isActive, name } = modal.user;

  try {
    if (modal.action === 'delete') {
      await axios.delete(`/user/${id}`, {
        headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${token}` }
      });
      setUsers(prevUsers => prevUsers.filter(u => u.id !== id));
      setNotification(`${name} was permanently removed from FlowGuard.`);
    } else {
      await axios.put(`/user/suspend/${id}`, {}, {
        headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${token}` }
      });
      setUsers(prevUsers => prevUsers.map(u => u.id === id ? { ...u, isActive: !isActive } : u));
    }
    closeModal();
  } catch (error) {
    alert(`Failed to ${modal.action === 'delete' ? 'remove' : 'update access for'} ${name}.`);
    console.error(error);
    closeModal();
  }
};
```

**Modal Rendering Pattern:**
```javascript
{modal.isOpen && (
  <div className="modal-overlay">
    <div className={`modal-content security-modal ${modal.action === 'delete' ? 'delete-variant' : ''}`}>
      <div className="modal-header">
        <span className="modal-icon">{...icon...}</span>
        <h3>{...title...}</h3>
      </div>
      <p>{...body text...}</p>
      <div className="modal-actions">
        <button className="cancel-btn" onClick={closeModal}>Cancel</button>
        <button className={`confirm-btn ${...conditional classes...}`} onClick={handleConfirmAction}>
          Confirm
        </button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
)}
```

---

### 2. Axios Call Pattern (StaffManagement.jsx & TenantManagement.jsx)

**GET Pattern (fetching data):**
```javascript
const token = localStorage.getItem("accessToken");

const codeRes = await axios.get('/user/my-code', {
  headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${token}` }
});
setCompanyCode(codeRes.data.companyCode);
```

**DELETE Pattern:**
```javascript
await axios.delete(`/user/${id}`, {
  headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${token}` }
});
setStaff(prev => prev.filter(m => m.id !== id));
triggerNotify(`${name} removed from system.`, "success");
```

**PUT Pattern (updates):**
```javascript
const res = await axios.put('/user/generate-code', {}, {
  headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${token}` }
});
setCompanyCode(res.data.companyCode);
triggerNotify("New security key generated!", "success");
```

**POST Pattern (create):**
```javascript
const res = await axios.post('/user/invite-tenant', {}, {
  headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${token}` }
});
setNewCode(res.data.inviteCode);
fetchInvites();
```

**Error Handling Pattern:**
```javascript
const triggerNotify = (msg, type = 'error') => {
  setNotification({ message: msg, type });
  setTimeout(() => setNotification({ message: '', type: '' }), 4000);
};

try {
  // API call
} catch (err) {
  triggerNotify("Operation failed: Database restriction.");
  closeDeleteModal();
}
```

---

### 3. Server Routes (incident.js)

**Existing Routes:**
- `POST /scan-frame` - AI frame processing with multer file upload
- `GET /` - Get all incident logs with search capability
- `GET /:id` - Get specific log by ID
- `DELETE /:id` - Delete a log

**Notable Missing Routes:**
- PATCH/PUT for updating incident logs
- POST for creating manual incident entries (only AI-driven creation exists)

---

### 4. Reusable CSS Classes for Forms/Inputs in Modals

**Modal Structure Classes:**
- `.modal-overlay` - Fixed overlay backdrop with blur (z-index: 2000)
- `.security-modal` - Modal content box (max-width: 450px, padding: 30px)
- `.modal-header` - Header section with icon and title
- `.modal-icon` - Icon element (font-size: 2.5rem)
- `.modal-actions` - Button container (flexbox, gap: 12px)

**Button Classes:**
- `.cancel-btn` - Gray cancel button (background: #334155)
- `.confirm-btn` - Base confirm button styling
- `.suspend-btn` - Red action button (background: #f43f5e)
- `.reactivate-btn` - Green action button (background: #10b981)
- `.delete-btn` - Derived from confirm-btn with delete styling

**Color/Status Classes:**
- `.status-badge` - Inline status indicator
- `.status-badge.active` - Green active state
- `.status-badge.expired` - Red expired state

**Animations:**
- `fadeIn` - Overlay fade-in (0.2s)
- `scaleUp` - Modal content scale animation (0.3s, cubic-bezier easing)

---

### Summary for Your Feature

**For a create/edit modal in your feature:**
1. Use same modal state pattern: `{ isOpen: false, data: null, action: 'create'|'edit' }`
2. Add form field state if needed: separate state or object like `{ field1: '', field2: '' }`
3. Use same token retrieval: `localStorage.getItem("accessToken")`
4. Follow axios pattern: GET for fetches, POST for create, PUT/PATCH for update, DELETE for remove
5. Always include `Authorization: Bearer ${token}` header
6. Use notification callback for feedback (replicate `triggerNotify` or Users.tsx notification pattern)
7. Reuse modal CSS classes and structure—they're already well-designed and consistent

