# Plan: Full CRUD — Incident Dashboard

## Context

The Incident Dashboard (`/incidents`) was built as a static-data-only shell in the previous session. The 12 hardcoded incidents live entirely in React state — deletes don't persist across refresh and there's no way to create or update records. This session wires all four CRUD operations to the real API and persists the test data to the DB so the dashboard behaves like production.

**Scope**: Backend model + routes → Frontend data layer → Create modal → Update (edit mode in detail modal) → Delete confirmation. No AI-triggered seeding (scan-frame). No changes to App.jsx, Sidebar.jsx, roles, or any page outside IncidentDashboard.

---

## Files to change (4 total)

