```js
severity: {
    type: DataTypes.STRING(20),
    allowNull: true,
    defaultValue: 'Medium'          // 'Critical' | 'High' | 'Medium' | 'Low'
},
source: {
    type: DataTypes.STRING(50),
    allowNull: true,
    defaultValue: 'Facial Recognition'  // 'Facial Recognition' | 'Object Detection' | 'Manual'
},
resolutionStatus: {
    type: DataTypes.STRING(50),
    allowNull: false,
    defaultValue: 'Active'          // 'Active' | 'Investigating' | 'Escalated to Security' | 'Cleared'
},
notes: {
    type: DataTypes.TEXT,
    allowNull: true,
    defaultValue: ''
}
```

Sequelize's `alter: true` sync (already in `server/index.js`) will `ALTER TABLE` automatically on next server start — no manual migration.

